<a href="http://www.csmenetwork.com/2/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=10018&amp;Itemid=211" target="_self">http://www.csmenetwork.com/2/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=artic...</a></p>		</div>
		
		
				<div class="box">
			<h3>Editorial comment</h3>
			<p>While the Commission communication claims that the results of the two previous phases of banana support are ‘generally positive’, it also admits that ‘certain challenges remain, particularly in countries where diversification was a priority’. Hence, it would appear critical that the start-up activities in early 2011 under the new 2010-2013 BAM budget address these challenges. At the same time, a sound balance should be kept, with efforts made towards increasing productivity, efficiency, and profitability of the ACP banana supply chains, especially in anticipation of further liberalisation of EU banana trade with the main competitors from Latin America. BAM activities should also continue to promote the compliance of ACP country producers with labour, health, and environmental standards, not only as a means of improving the living standards within a specific sector, but in consideration of the spillover effects this may have on other parts of the economy, and its overall contribution to socio-economic stability.</p>
		</div>
		
